=================================================
libm210 - API for Pegasus Mobile NoteTaker M210.
=================================================

.. contents::

Description
===========

The Code Grove libm210 project provides a library to communicate with
Pegasus Mobile NoteTaker Tablet.

General information
===================

- **Author**: Tuomas Räsänen (tuos) <tuos@codegrove.org>
- **Homepage**: http://codegrove.org/libm210/
- **License**: GPLv3+ (see COPYING for details)
- **Version**: 0.2

Build requirements
==================

- libudev-dev

Runtime requirements
====================

- libudev

Downloading
===========

- Ubuntu package: https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove
- Tarball is available at: http://codegrove.org/libm210/releases/libm210-0.2.tar.gz
- Tarballs of every release at: http://codegrove.org/libm210/releases/
- Latest sources from public git-repository: http://github.com/tuos/libm210/ ::

    git clone git://github.com/tuos/libm210.git

Installing
==========

Ubuntu
------

The recommended way to install libm210 is to
`add it's PPA to your system <https://launchpad.net/~tuos/+archive/codegrove>`_.
This allows you to treat libm210 as any other Ubuntu package.

Other systems
-------------

The install-procedure adheres the "standard"::

  ./configure
  make && make install

Bug reporting
=============

Report bugs by sending email to tuos@codegrove.org or by opening an issue
at http://github.com/tuos/libm210/issues .
